<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2013/08/23/spring-batch-3-0-milestone-1-released">Spring Batch 3.0 Milestone 1 Released</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/ab8031806cdd258238e67411157d215a?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/mminella">Michael Minella</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2013-08-23 03:03:00.0">August 23, 2013</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="1144" href="/blog/2013/08/23/spring-batch-3-0-milestone-1-released#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p></p>
<p>Today we are pleased to announce the first milestone release towards Spring Batch 3.0 (<a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/dist.springframework.org/milestone/BATCH/spring-batch-3.0.0.M1-no-dependencies.zip" onclick="javascript:urchinTracker('/outbound/s3.amazonaws.com');">download</a>). With this release we take our first steps towards implementing the JSR-352 Java Batch specification. Spring Batch is a lightweight, comprehensive framework for the development of robust batch applications.</p>
<br>
<h2>JSR-352</h2>
<br>
<p>JSR-352 is billed as the standardization of batch processing for the java platform. As part of that standardization, this JSR has included three main pieces:</p>
<br>
<ul>
<br>
<li>A XML based DSL for configuring jobs</li>
<br>
<li>An API for creating job related components (readers/writers/etc)</li>
<br>
<li>An API and description of behavior for a supporting classes and concepts</li>
<br>
</ul>
</div>
</section>
<a class="blog-preview--readmore desktop-only" href="/blog/2013/08/23/spring-batch-3-0-milestone-1-released">
Read more...
</a>
</article>
